Lucha libre originated in [MASK]."
Lucha libre is especially famous for its colourful [MASK].
In lucha libre, a wrestler’s mask represents their [MASK].
Mask vs. mask matches are called 'Máscara contra [MASK].'.
Losing a máscara match usually means a luchador must [MASK].
Mask vs. hair matches are known as 'Máscara contra [MASK].'.
The terms 'técnico' and 'rudo' describe a wrestler’s [MASK].
Técnicos are usually portrayed as the [MASK].
The bad guys in lucha libre are known as [MASK].
El [MASK] is considered one of the most famous luchadores of all time.
Blue [MASK] was a famous rival of El Santo.
Rey [MASK] popularized lucha libre in American wrestling.
[MASK] is the oldest active wrestling promotion in the world.
Lucha libre crowds often throw [MASK] at villains.
A luchador’s real [MASK] is often kept secret.
The wrestling ring in Mexico is commonly called the [MASK].
Taking someone’s [MASK] is considered the ultimate humiliation in lucha libre.
Good guys in wrestling are traditionally called [MASK].
Bad guys in wrestling are known as [MASK].
A wrestler who turns evil is said to turn [MASK].
Wrestling storylines are commonly referred to as [MASK].
Championship belts are often called championship [MASK].
[MASK] are spoken segments used to build storyline.
A planned dramatic moment in a match is called a [MASK].
A match that appears unplanned or real is known as a [MASK].
Failing to execute a move properly is known as a [MASK].
Exaggerating pain to make moves look effective is called [MASK].
An wrestler who loses frequently is called a [MASK].
The final match of a show is known as the [MASK].
A popular wrestler is said to be '[MASK]' with the crowd.
